Class MsgClasses

    • Field Detail

      • REQUEST

        public static final int REQUEST
        Consumers use RequestMsg to express interest in a new stream or modify some parameters on an existing stream; typically results in the delivery of a RefreshMsg or StatusMsg.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REFRESH

        public static final int REFRESH
        The Interactive Provider can use this class to respond to a consumer's request for information (solicited) or provide a data resynchronization point (unsolicited). The NIP can use this class to initiate a data flow on a new item stream. Conveys state information, QoS, stream permissioning information, and group information in addition to payload.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • STATUS

        public static final int STATUS
        Indicates changes to the stream or data properties. A provider uses StatusMsg to close streams and to indicate successful establishment of a stream when there is no data to convey. This message can indicate changes:
        • In streamState or dataState
        • In a stream's permissioning information
        • To the item group to which the stream belongs
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • UPDATE

        public static final int UPDATE
        Interactive or NIPs use UpdateMsg to convey changes to information on a stream. Update messages typically flow on a stream after delivery of a refresh
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CLOSE

        public static final int CLOSE
        A consumer uses CloseMsg to indicate no further interest in a stream. As a result, the stream should be closed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ACK

        public static final int ACK
        A provider uses AckMsg to inform a consumer of success or failure for a specific PostMsg or CloseMsg.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • GENERIC

        public static final int GENERIC
        A bi-directional message that does not have any implicit interaction semantics associated with it, thus the name generic. After a stream is established via a request-refresh/status interaction:
        • A consumer can send this message to a provider.
        • A provider can send this message to a consumer.
        • NIPs can send this message to the ADH/
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • POST

        public static final int POST
        A consumer uses PostMsg to push content upstream. This information can be applied to an Enterprise Platform cache or routed further upstream to a data source. After receiving posted data, upstream components can republish it to downstream consumers.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
